# Changelog (mandatory for notable changes)

## Canonical file

- **`CHANGELOG.md`** (repo root) — human-readable history of user- and operator-visible fixes and features, plus notable engineering changes.

## When to add an entry

In the **same change** as the work, add a bullet under **`## [Unreleased]`** in **`CHANGELOG.md`** when you change anything that affects **what ships** or **how the app behaves**, including:

- **`api/`**, **`web/`**, **`Dockerfile`**, **`docker-compose.yml`**, root **`package.json`** / lockfile in a way that changes the built image or dependencies
- **Drizzle migrations** or **`api/src/db/schema.ts`**

## When you may skip

Skip a changelog line **only** when the diff cannot affect operators, build output, or runtime — for example:

- **`docs/`**-only edits (excluding this file when you are recording other work in the same commit)
- **Comment-only** or **whitespace-only** in code
- **`.cursor/`** rule tweaks that do not change product behaviour

If you are unsure, add a one-line **`### Changed`** or **`### Fixed`** note — prefer being explicit.

## How to write entries

- Short **imperative** or **past** summary; name the **area** (e.g. Web, API, Docker) when helpful.
- Link deep internals to **`docs/`** in prose only if operators care; otherwise stay high-level.

## Process link

This rule is part of the same workflow as **`local-docker-deploy.mdc`**, **`git-commits.mdc`**, and **[`AGENTS.md`](../AGENTS.md)** (development process + end-of-task checklist). Do not mark a coding task complete without **`CHANGELOG.md`** updated when an entry is required.

A **changelog-worthy** slice often matches **one Git commit** — see **`git-commits.mdc`** for committing each logical unit separately.
